pokemon.name: bulbasaur
pokemon.text_entry: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

pokemon.name: ivysaur
pokemon.text_entry: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.

pokemon.name: venusaur
pokemon.text_entry: Huge amounts of pollen burst from it with the force of a volcanic eruption. Breathing in too much of the pollen can cause fainting.

pokemon.name: charmander
pokemon.text_entry: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

pokemon.name: charmeleon
pokemon.text_entry: If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings.

pokemon.name: charizard
pokemon.text_entry: The flame inside its body burns hotter than 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit. When Charizard roars, that temperature climbs even higher.

pokemon.name: squirtle
pokemon.text_entry: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

pokemon.name: wartortle
pokemon.text_entry: It cleverly controls its furry ears and tail to maintain its balance while swimming.

pokemon.name: blastoise
pokemon.text_entry: Water fired from this Pokémon’s central main cannon has enough power to blast a hole into a mountain.

pokemon.name: caterpie
pokemon.text_entry: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

pokemon.name: metapod
pokemon.text_entry: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can’t withstand a harsh attack.

pokemon.name: butterfree
pokemon.text_entry: Once it has opponents trapped in a tornado that could blow away a 10-ton truck, it finishes them off with its poisonous scales.

pokemon.name: weedle
pokemon.text_entry: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

pokemon.name: kakuna
pokemon.text_entry: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

pokemon.name: beedrill
pokemon.text_entry: Its legs have become poison stingers. It stabs its prey repeatedly with the stingers on its limbs, dealing the final blow with the stinger on its rear.

pokemon.name: pidgey
pokemon.text_entry: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

pokemon.name: pidgeotto
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

pokemon.name: pidgeot
pokemon.text_entry: With its muscular strength now greatly increased, it can fly continuously for two weeks without resting.

pokemon.name: rattata
pokemon.text_entry: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

pokemon.name: raticate
pokemon.text_entry: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

pokemon.name: spearow
pokemon.text_entry: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

pokemon.name: fearow
pokemon.text_entry: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

pokemon.name: ekans
pokemon.text_entry: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

pokemon.name: arbok
pokemon.text_entry: The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

pokemon.name: pikachu
pokemon.text_entry: When it smashes its opponents with its bolt- shaped tail, it delivers a surge of electricity equivalent to a lightning strike.

pokemon.name: raichu
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon rides on its tail while it uses its psychic powers to levitate. It attacks with star-shaped thunderbolts.

pokemon.name: sandshrew
pokemon.text_entry: It lives in snowy mountains on southern islands. When a blizzard rolls in, this Pokémon hunkers down in the snow to avoid getting blown away.

pokemon.name: sandslash
pokemon.text_entry: Many people climb snowy mountains, hoping to see the icy spikes of these Pokémon glistening in the light of dawn.

pokemon.name: nidoran-f
pokemon.text_entry: A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like to fight. Beware—its small horn secretes venom.

pokemon.name: nidorina
pokemon.text_entry: When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

pokemon.name: nidoqueen
pokemon.text_entry: Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pokémon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

pokemon.name: nidoran-m
pokemon.text_entry: Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.

pokemon.name: nidorino
pokemon.text_entry: Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an enemy with the horn, the impact makes the poison leak out.

pokemon.name: nidoking
pokemon.text_entry: Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

pokemon.name: clefairy
pokemon.text_entry: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. However, this cute Pokémon is rarely found.

pokemon.name: clefable
pokemon.text_entry: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they’re usually found in quiet places.

pokemon.name: vulpix
pokemon.text_entry: If you observe its curly hairs through a microscope, you’ll see small ice particles springing up.

pokemon.name: ninetales
pokemon.text_entry: While it will guide travelers who get lost on a snowy mountain down to the mountain’s base, it won’t forgive anyone who harms nature.

pokemon.name: jigglypuff
pokemon.text_entry: By freely changing the wavelength of its voice, Jigglypuff sings a mysterious melody sure to make any listener sleepy.

pokemon.name: wigglytuff
pokemon.text_entry: It’s proud of its fur, which is fine and delicate. In particular, the curl on its forehead has a texture that’s perfectly heavenly.

pokemon.name: zubat
pokemon.text_entry: Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

pokemon.name: golbat
pokemon.text_entry: It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

pokemon.name: oddish
pokemon.text_entry: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

pokemon.name: gloom
pokemon.text_entry: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

pokemon.name: vileplume
pokemon.text_entry: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

pokemon.name: paras
pokemon.text_entry: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

pokemon.name: parasect
pokemon.text_entry: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

pokemon.name: venonat
pokemon.text_entry: Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

pokemon.name: venomoth
pokemon.text_entry: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

pokemon.name: diglett
pokemon.text_entry: Its three hairs change shape depending on Diglett’s mood. They’re a useful communication tool among these Pokémon.

pokemon.name: dugtrio
pokemon.text_entry: These Diglett triplets dig over 60 miles below sea level. No one knows what it’s like underground.

pokemon.name: meowth
pokemon.text_entry: These daring Pokémon have coins on their foreheads. Darker coins are harder, and harder coins garner more respect among Meowth.

pokemon.name: persian
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is one tough opponent. Not only does it have formidable physical abilities, but it’s also not above fighting dirty.

pokemon.name: psyduck
pokemon.text_entry: As Psyduck gets stressed out, its headache gets progressively worse. It uses intense psychic energy to overwhelm those around it.

pokemon.name: golduck
pokemon.text_entry: Old tales tell of Golduck punishing those that defiled its river. The guilty were dragged into the water and taken away.

pokemon.name: mankey
pokemon.text_entry: An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

pokemon.name: primeape
pokemon.text_entry: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

pokemon.name: growlithe
pokemon.text_entry: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

pokemon.name: arcanine
pokemon.text_entry: A Pokémon that has long been admired for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

pokemon.name: poliwag
pokemon.text_entry: In rivers with fast-flowing water, this Pokémon will cling to a rock by using its thick lips, which act like a suction cup.

pokemon.name: poliwhirl
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon’s sweat is a slimy mucus. When captured, Poliwhirl can slither from its enemies’ grasp and escape.

pokemon.name: poliwrath
pokemon.text_entry: Poliwrath is skilled at both swimming and martial arts. It uses its well-trained arms to dish out powerful punches.

pokemon.name: abra
pokemon.text_entry: Abra can teleport in its sleep. Apparently the more deeply Abra sleeps, the farther its teleportations go.

pokemon.name: kadabra
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon’s telekinesis is immensely powerful. To prepare for evolution, Kadabra stores up psychic energy in the star on its forehead.

pokemon.name: alakazam
pokemon.text_entry: Alakazam wields potent psychic powers. It’s said that this Pokémon used these powers to create the spoons it holds.

pokemon.name: machop
pokemon.text_entry: Always brimming with power, it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

pokemon.name: machoke
pokemon.text_entry: Its formidable body never gets tired. It helps people by doing work such as the moving of heavy goods.

pokemon.name: machamp
pokemon.text_entry: With four arms that react more quickly than it can think, it can execute many punches at once.

pokemon.name: bellsprout
pokemon.text_entry: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

pokemon.name: weepinbell
pokemon.text_entry: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

pokemon.name: victreebel
pokemon.text_entry: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

pokemon.name: tentacool
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is mostly made of water. A Tentacool out in the ocean is very hard to spot, because its body blends in with the sea.

pokemon.name: tentacruel
pokemon.text_entry: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and shrink freely. Tentacruel ensnares prey in a net of spread-out tentacles, delivering venomous stings to its catch.

pokemon.name: geodude
pokemon.text_entry: Its stone head is imbued with electricity and magnetism. If you carelessly step on one, you’ll be in for a painful shock.

pokemon.name: graveler
pokemon.text_entry: When it comes rolling down a mountain path, anything in its way gets zapped by electricity and sent flying.

pokemon.name: golem
pokemon.text_entry: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s exposed to air.

pokemon.name: ponyta
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon will look into your eyes and read the contents of your heart. If it finds evil there, it promptly hides away.

pokemon.name: rapidash
pokemon.text_entry: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd’s pace and direction of travel.

pokemon.name: slowpoke
pokemon.text_entry: When this Pokémon’s tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokémon.

pokemon.name: slowbro
pokemon.text_entry: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

pokemon.name: magnemite
pokemon.text_entry: It subsists on electricity. As Magnemite flies, it emits electromagnetic waves from the units on each side of its body.

pokemon.name: magneton
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is constantly putting out a powerful magnetic force. Most computers go haywire when a Magneton approaches.

pokemon.name: farfetchd
pokemon.text_entry: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

pokemon.name: doduo
pokemon.text_entry: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

pokemon.name: dodrio
pokemon.text_entry: One of Doduo’s two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

pokemon.name: seel
pokemon.text_entry: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: dewgong
pokemon.text_entry: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

pokemon.name: grimer
pokemon.text_entry: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

pokemon.name: muk
pokemon.text_entry: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

pokemon.name: shellder
pokemon.text_entry: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

pokemon.name: cloyster
pokemon.text_entry: Once it slams its shell shut, it is impossible to open, even by those with superior strength.

pokemon.name: gastly
pokemon.text_entry: With its gas-like body, it can sneak into any place it desires. However, it can be blown away by wind.

pokemon.name: haunter
pokemon.text_entry: If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.

pokemon.name: gengar
pokemon.text_entry: It lays traps, hoping to steal the lives of those it catches. If you stand in front of its mouth, you’ll hear your loved ones’ voices calling out to you.

pokemon.name: onix
pokemon.text_entry: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

pokemon.name: drowzee
pokemon.text_entry: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

pokemon.name: hypno
pokemon.text_entry: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

pokemon.name: krabby
pokemon.text_entry: If it senses danger approaching, it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

pokemon.name: kingler
pokemon.text_entry: The bubbles it spews out are strongly alkaline. Any opponents hit by them will have their bodies quickly melted away.

pokemon.name: voltorb
pokemon.text_entry: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

pokemon.name: electrode
pokemon.text_entry: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

pokemon.name: exeggcute
pokemon.text_entry: These Pokémon get nervous when they’re not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

pokemon.name: exeggutor
pokemon.text_entry: When they work together, Exeggutor’s three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

pokemon.name: cubone
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon wears the skull of its deceased mother. Sometimes Cubone’s dreams make it cry, but each tear Cubone sheds makes it stronger.

pokemon.name: marowak
pokemon.text_entry: When this Pokémon evolved, the skull of its mother fused to it. Marowak’s temperament also turned vicious at the same time.

pokemon.name: hitmonlee
pokemon.text_entry: The legs freely contract and stretch. The stretchy legs allow it to hit a distant foe with a rising kick.

pokemon.name: hitmonchan
pokemon.text_entry: Its punches slice the air. However, it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.

pokemon.name: lickitung
pokemon.text_entry: Bug Pokémon are Lickitung’s main food source. This Pokémon paralyzes its prey with a lick from its long tongue, then swallows the prey whole.

pokemon.name: koffing
pokemon.text_entry: It adores polluted air. Some claim that Koffing used to be more plentiful in the Galar region than they are now.

pokemon.name: weezing
pokemon.text_entry: Long ago, during a time when droves of factories fouled the air with pollution, Weezing changed into this form for some reason.

pokemon.name: rhyhorn
pokemon.text_entry: It can remember only one thing at a time. Once it starts rushing, it forgets why it started.

pokemon.name: rhydon
pokemon.text_entry: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: chansey
pokemon.text_entry: This species was once very slow. To protect their eggs from other creatures, these Pokémon became able to flee quickly.

pokemon.name: tangela
pokemon.text_entry: The vines of a Tangela have a distinct scent. In some parts of Galar, Tangela vines are used as herbs.

pokemon.name: kangaskhan
pokemon.text_entry: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

pokemon.name: horsea
pokemon.text_entry: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

pokemon.name: seadra
pokemon.text_entry: Seadra’s mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that’s larger than the opening of its mouth.

pokemon.name: goldeen
pokemon.text_entry: Its dorsal and pectoral fins are strongly developed like muscles. It can swim at a speed of five knots.

pokemon.name: seaking
pokemon.text_entry: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

pokemon.name: staryu
pokemon.text_entry: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn’t bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

pokemon.name: starmie
pokemon.text_entry: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

pokemon.name: mr-mime
pokemon.text_entry: It’s known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

pokemon.name: scyther
pokemon.text_entry: If you come across an area in a forest where a lot of the trees have been cut down, what you’ve found is a Scyther’s territory.

pokemon.name: jynx
pokemon.text_entry: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

pokemon.name: electabuzz
pokemon.text_entry: If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pokémon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

pokemon.name: magmar
pokemon.text_entry: Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

pokemon.name: pinsir
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

pokemon.name: tauros
pokemon.text_entry: The Tauros of the Galar region are volatile in nature, and they won’t allow people to ride on their backs.

pokemon.name: magikarp
pokemon.text_entry: This weak and pathetic Pokémon gets easily pushed along rivers when there are strong currents.

pokemon.name: gyarados
pokemon.text_entry: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

pokemon.name: lapras
pokemon.text_entry: It surrounds itself with a huge ring of gathered ice particles. It uses the ring to smash any icebergs that might impede its graceful swimming.

pokemon.name: ditto
pokemon.text_entry: When it encounters another Ditto, it will move faster than normal to duplicate that opponent exactly.

pokemon.name: eevee
pokemon.text_entry: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

pokemon.name: vaporeon
pokemon.text_entry: Its body’s cellular structure is similar to the molecular composition of water. It can melt invisibly in water.

pokemon.name: jolteon
pokemon.text_entry: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10,000-volt lightning bolts.

pokemon.name: flareon
pokemon.text_entry: It stores some of the air it inhales in its internal flame pouch, which heats it to over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

pokemon.name: porygon
pokemon.text_entry: In recent years, this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokémon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.

pokemon.name: omanyte
pokemon.text_entry: An ancient Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

pokemon.name: omastar
pokemon.text_entry: Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

pokemon.name: kabuto
pokemon.text_entry: A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

pokemon.name: kabutops
pokemon.text_entry: A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

pokemon.name: aerodactyl
pokemon.text_entry: The power of Mega Evolution has completely restored its genes. The rocks on its body are harder than diamond.

pokemon.name: snorlax
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon’s stomach is so strong, even eating moldy or rotten food will not affect it.

pokemon.name: articuno
pokemon.text_entry: A legendary bird Pokémon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

pokemon.name: zapdos
pokemon.text_entry: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

pokemon.name: moltres
pokemon.text_entry: A legendary bird Pokémon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

pokemon.name: dratini
pokemon.text_entry: Long thought to be a myth, this Pokémon’s existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

pokemon.name: dragonair
pokemon.text_entry: According to a witness, its body was surrounded by a strange aura that gave it a mystical look.

pokemon.name: dragonite
pokemon.text_entry: It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, these are only rumors.

pokemon.name: mewtwo
pokemon.text_entry: Psychic power has augmented its muscles. It has a grip strength of one ton and can sprint a hundred meters in two seconds flat!

pokemon.name: mew
pokemon.text_entry: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.
